matches

public boolean matches(java.util.Map attrs)
                throws DSMLProfileException
If more the one of initial, any, or final is set, this does a logical or.

If you don't want that behavior, nest substrings filters with one item in the logical operator that you want.

Overrides:
matches in class FilterItem
Parameters:
attrs -
Returns:
true any of the fields match any of the values of the attribute of the same name as this filter from the attrs map.
